@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "TriOtix" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  To move a bar, it must be beside the empty space, which is
indicated by a small dot. Clicking on part of a bar which is next
to the empty space will make the bar rotate towards the empty
space.

  One thing to remember is that the 'figure 8' shaped bars can
rotate and be placed in any position, that is: horizontally,
vertically and diagonally. However, the coloured bar can only be
placed horizontally and vertically.

  When a portion of the coloured bar is placed on the exit at the
bottom of the game board (where the small square is located), the
game is completed... Complete the game in the least amount of
moves.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

